The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Kuala Lumpur, May 30 (PTI): Malaysia has withdrawn the visa-on-arrival facility for Indians and Bangladeshis, who will now need a two-week social visit pass and a return ticket to visit the country.           
	Home minister Syed Hamid Albar said the rules were part of efforts to overcome the problem of illegal immigrants. The social visit pass must be obtained from the tourists home country.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): Pakistani human rights activist Ansar Burney, who fought for the release of Kashmir Singh and Sarabjit Singh on death row in Pakistan, was deported from here to Dubai on Friday, sources said. Burney, who was the human rights minister in the interim government in Pakistan, was deported because of a look-out notice against him, they said.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): The national consumer commission has asked an insurance company, which rejected a factorys fire cover claim, to pay Rs 56 lakh with interest and Rs 1.5 lakh for litigation costs. The panel said the rejection of the Punjab-based oil firms claim by the United India Insurance Company Ltd was unfair trade practice and unjustified.                  
	Thrissur (PTI): An idol and several valuable articles, including a silver crown, were stolen from the Sree Ramaswamy temple at Thriprayar near here on Friday, police said. Two securitymen, who were on duty at night, said they did not notice the robbers as it was raining heavily.                   
	Nagpur (PTI): The hot weather trial phase of the Tejas light combat aircraft programme went off successfully, sources said on Friday. The aircraft was flown from Bangalore to Nagpur in an hour with more than adequate fuel. This was the first operation ferry flight of the Tejas with external drop tanks.                                                                                                                         
